title: Jorvic Way Walking Route
description: A circular walk through the countryside surrounding the city of York. Starting at Tadcaster the walk visits the 18th century Beningbrough Hall and Park (video below), Wheldrake , Esrick and Bolton Percy. The route also visits Marston Moor, Hagg Wood , the confluence of the Rivers Nidd and Ouse at Moor Monkton and the Moorlands Nature Reserve. There are also long riverside sections along the River Great Ouse and the River Derwent near Dunnington.
